ZH: 这层树木可以掩蔽我们的踪迹。
EN: This layer of trees can conceal our tracks.

ZH: 他戴着帽子来掩蔽他的脸。
EN: He wore a hat to mask his face.

ZH: 防空洞掩蔽了村民们的安全。
EN: The air raid shelter concealed the safety of the villagers.

ZH: 在厚重的云层中，太阳被掩蔽了。
EN: The sun was concealed by thick clouds.

ZH: 她用伞掩蔽着她的头发，以免被雨水打湿。
EN: She used an umbrella to shield her hair from getting wet in the rain.

ZH: 他在暗处掩蔽，以便能更好地窃听谈话内容。
EN: He concealed himself in the dark to eavesdrop on the conversation.

ZH: 枯叶掩蔽了土地的枯黄。
EN: The fallen leaves masked the barrenness of the land.

ZH: 政府试图掩蔽事故的真相。
EN: The government attempted to cover up the truth of the accident.

ZH: 城市的灯光掩蔽了星星的闪耀。
EN: The city lights obscured the twinkle of the stars.

ZH: 他掩蔽住耳朵，以免听见令他恼火的声音。
EN: He covered his ears to block out the annoying sound.

ZH: 绿树掩蔽了房屋，为其提供了一些遮蔽。
EN: The green trees provided some shelter, concealing the houses.

ZH: 我扔掉了那些文件，以免掩蔽我的过去。
EN: I got rid of those documents to hide my past.

ZH: 她用手臂掩蔽住阳光，以便能清楚地看书。
EN: She shielded her eyes from the sun with her arm so that she could read clearly.

ZH: 雾浓得几乎掩蔽了整个山谷。
EN: The fog was so thick that it almost obscured the entire valley.

ZH: 他把自己藏得很好，几乎掩蔽了他的存在。
EN: He hid himself so well that he almost concealed his presence.

ZH: 过去的谣言被真相所掩蔽。
EN: The past rumors were overshadowed by the truth.

ZH: 行人们挤在一起，掩蔽了道路的通行。
EN: The pedestrians crowded together, blocking the passage of the road.

ZH: 沙丘掩蔽了沙漠中的植物。
EN: The sand dunes concealed the plants in the desert.

ZH: 大雨掩蔽了远处山脉的轮廓。
EN: The heavy rain obscured the outline of the distant mountains.

ZH: 盛开的花朵掩蔽了长满枯叶的地面。
EN: The blooming flowers concealed the ground covered with dead leaves.

ZH: 她的微笑掩蔽了内心的痛苦。
EN: Her smile masked the pain inside her heart.
